Alzheimer's:

• Alzheimer's is the most common form of dementia
• Dementia is the inability of the brain to function properly due to old age
• It is a degenerative neurological disorder 

Symptoms to look for:

• Difficulty in recognizing known people or things
• Inability to remember recent activities or events
• Forgetting common words while speaking, reading or writing
• Inability to do routine chores like bathing, grooming or eating
• Highly emotional behaviour
• Depression and anxiety

Causes:

• Gradual fall in level of neurotransmitters in the brain, which are responsible for transmitting messages in the brain
• Presence of abnormal protein bundles in brain which leads to loss of connection between the brain cells

